Hi,

It is not an async program. The code checks some GPIO pins in a while loop and make appropriate state transitions based on the value of the GPIO pins. The simplified code is as follows:

```
def timer_callback():
    fsm.timer_fired()

    while True:
    if GPIO.input(pin1):
        fsm.got_high()
        time.sleep(0.05)
    else:
            threading.Timer(60, timer_callback).start()
            fsm.got_low()

    if GPIO.input(pin2):
        fsm.myevent1()
    else:
        fsm.myevent()
```

In the above code, I think the async event transition happens in the `timer_callback` thread. In my case the `timer_callback` thread can wait if any event is in progress and do the state transition only after any in-progress event is complete. But how can I implement this check?

