Hey @blueyed, thanks for the report! It looks like the tests were (incorrectly) asserting that after deleting a resource, the resource would still be an instance of whatever class it was before being deleted. This used to work because stripe-mock was (also incorrectly) returning fixtures with the `object: <name>` attribute for deleted resources.

@tmaxwell-stripe recently updated the OpenAPI spec and fixtures (used by stripe-mock) to correctly represent deleted resources, and so those tests are now failing. This is easy enough to fix, we just need a new numbered version of stripe-mock.

@tmaxwell-stripe: Mind cutting a new stripe-mock version with the latest OpenAPI spec?

cc @stripe/api-libraries: We should check if other libraries are affected by this issue too.

